Australian Prime Minister Visits S.Korea 
Australian Prime Minister John Howard arrived here Thursday night for a
four-day visit at the invitation of South Korean President Kim
Dae-jung.
Howard is expected meet with President Kim to exchange views on
strengthening relations between the two countries, especially on
Australia's policy toward the Democratic People's Republic of Korea
(DPRK) after the relations restored between Pyongyang and Sydney.
Meanwhile, Howard will introduce the background of restoration of the
diplomatic relationship between Australia and the DPRK.
Early this month, Australia became the second western country, after
Italy, to establish ties with the DPRK after nearly 25 years without
links.
During his stay in South Korea, Howard is also scheduled to meet Prime
Minister Park Tae-joon and South Korean business leaders.
